description: Potential Global Subsidence in  2040 is a raster dataset representing the classified probabilities of land subsidence based on a six-level equal interval scale (very low, low, medium-low, medium-high, high, and very high). The data helps in understanding the potential impact of post-glacial rebound and sea-level rise on coastal regions.
